  <title>Add a Time Record</title>

  <p>To add a new time record:</p>
  <steps>
    <item><p>Log in to the Control Panel.</p></item>
    <item><p>Click the <gui style="tab">Time Records</gui> tab.</p></item>
    <item><p>Select <guiseq><gui style="menu">Edit</gui><gui style="menuitem">Add</gui></guiseq>, or press <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>I</key></keyseq>, or click <gui style="button">Add</gui> in the toolbar.</p></item>
    <item><p>Select an employee and set other information, then click <gui style="button">Save</gui>.</p></item>
  </steps>

  <note style="important">
    <p>A time record should always have an employee owner. Also, unless it has an open end, the end date and time should be after the start date and time.</p>
    <p>The end date automatically changes to match the start date when the start date is changed to make editing easier.</p>
  </note>

